CONGRATULATIONS are in order for singer Rethabile Khumalo. This after she recently got engaged. This was announced by her mother Winnie Khumalo, who is also a singer. She wrote: “Congratulations my nunus on your engagement.” The message was accompanied by a video clip of Rethabile also announcing the news. In the clip, she can be seen screaming with excitement. “Hi guys, today turned out to be one of the best days of my life because I said yes. I got engaged today. Oh my God,” she said. ALSO READ : DANCING DINEO IS BACK! She then flashed her engagement ring for all to see. Her industry friends and fans took turns to congratulate her. Busi Kunene posted: “Congratulations, Retha. You deserve all the happiness coming your way. Winnie ukuzala ukuzelula, literally.” Themba commented: “Congratulations, ntwana yami. I’m so proud of you.” Mpumi Somandla wrote: “Congratulations to your baby girl.” Rethabile rose to fame when she was featured on the hit song Umlilo by DJ Zinhle. She has since ventured into a solo music career, and collaborated with artists such as Master KG. A post shared by winnie khumalo (@winnie_khumalo) 